2002-09-18 11:24  matt

	* README: Updated for Version 1.0a2.

2002-09-17 20:13  matt

	* doc/demos/: customtext.py, domtext.py, dummyfuncs.py, fstext.py,
	twtext.py: Dummy funcs provides dummy implementations of the
	showContent(), showAtts(), glimpse(), and unGlimpse() functions
	just to prove they work--though you can't tell for showAtts()
	because there is no default key or mouse binding for it.

2002-09-17 20:12  matt

	* texttree.py: TextTree.__init__ receives the funcs keyword
	argument and passes it to TreeWidget.__init__.

2002-09-17 20:11  matt

	* node.py: Modified double-click binding to invoke
	TreeWidget.showContent.

2002-09-17 20:10  matt

	* widget.py: Implemented the following public instance methods for
	TreeWidget.  - showContent(node)   Display the contents, e.g. in a
	text window.  - showAtts(node)	    Display the node's attributes. 
	- glimpse(node)       Display a glimpse of the node's content.	-
	unGlimpse(node)     Undo whatever the glimpse() methods did.  By
	default these are no-ops. To make them do something useful you must
	provide a 'funcs' dictionary when creating the TreeWidget instance.
	See the API docs for more info.
	
	Added default key bindings for the Enter and Escape keys. Enter
	invokes showContent, and Escape deselects the selected node.

